Project Scope Management is a process that helps project managers determine, document, and manage the goals, tasks, deliverables, deadlines, and budgets of a project. It is an essential element in project management that ensures maximum efficiency, eliminates unnecessary work, and keeps all team members on the same page.

Project Scope Management includes three main processes: planning, controlling, and closing.

To define the scope of a project, you must identify the project objectives, goals, sub-phases, tasks, resources, budget, schedule, and establish the parameters of the project by defining exactly what is included in the project and what is not

Project management software can also be used to help manage projects effectively by providing tools for tracking progress, managing resources, and communicating with team members. Examples include Kissflow Project and other popular project management software solutions.
